Row-column multiplication is the sum of the entry-by-entry products (first
 entry times first entry plus second entry times second entry plus third
 entry times third entry):
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
-1 & 0 & -3\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{c}
6\\
-2\\
5
\end{array}\right] & =-1(6)+0(-2)+(-3)(5)\\
 & =-6+0-15=-21.
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

