 tail of the first addend and head coinciding with the head of the last
 addend.
 In this case, the tail of the first addend is at 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

 and the head of the last addend is at 
\begin_inset Formula $(5,3)$
\end_inset

, so the answer is the vector from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $(5,3)$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{c}
5\\
3
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

