\frac{2}{\sqrt{3}}\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{c}
\frac{2}{\sqrt{3}}\end{array}\right]M=\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

There is no formula.
 We just have to recognize that the matrix in question is the 
\begin_inset Formula $1\times1$
\end_inset

 matrix with its lone entry equal to the reciprocal of 
\begin_inset Formula $\begin{array}{c}
\frac{2}{\sqrt{3}}\end{array}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
\frac{2}{\sqrt{3}}\end{array}\right]^{-1}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}\end{array}\right]
\]

