\end{array}\right]\stackrel[\frac{1}{2}A_{2,:}\to A_{2,:}]{\frac{1}{2}A_{1,:}\to A_{1,:}}{\longrightarrow}\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & \frac{19}{2}\\
0 & 1 & -\frac{7}{2}\\
0 & 0 & 0
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset

which means 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{3}$
\end_inset

 is a free variable and the solution is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x_{1}=-\frac{19}{2}x_{3};\quad x_{2}=\frac{7}{2}x_{3}.
\]

\end_inset

In parametric vector form, using 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 for the arbitrary parameter:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
x_{1}\\
x_{2}\\
x_{3}
\end{array}\right]=r\left[\begin{array}{c}
-\frac{19}{2}\\
\frac{7}{2}\\
1
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

Equivalently,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
x_{1}\\
x_{2}\\
x_{3}
\end{array}\right]=s\left[\begin{array}{c}
-19\\
7\\
2
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset


