, the 
\begin_inset Formula $i,\!j$
\end_inset

-entry of 
\begin_inset Formula $LR$
\end_inset

 is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
(LR)_{i,j}=L_{i,1}R_{1,j}+L_{i,2}R_{2,j}+\cdots+L_{i,s}R_{s,j}.\label{eq:entry-of-product-general}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Now suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell\times m$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

