Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S=\left\{ 1+2t,3+t-2t^{2},-5+4t^{2},-5t-2t^{2}\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is a 4-element subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}_{2}(\mathbb{R})$
\end_inset

, which has dimension 3, we know that 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is linearly dependent (theorem 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "thm:basis-superset"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 Hence the equation 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
A(1+2t)+B(3+t-2t^{2})+C(-5+4t^{2})+D(-5t-2t^{2})=0\label{eq:lin-ind-relationship}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 has nontrivial solutions.
 We need to find one.
 Expanding the lefthand side and collecting like terms:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
A+2At+3B+Bt-2Bt^{2}-5C+4Ct^{2}-5Dt-2Dt^{2} & =0\\
(A+3B-5C)+(2A+B-5D)t+(-2B+4C-2D)t^{2} & =0
\end{align*}

\end_inset

For this equation to be true (for all 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

, making the lefthand side equal to the zero function, the zero vector of
 the vector space), it must be that each coefficient is zero, giving the
 linear system
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
A+3B-5C & =0\\
2A+B-5D & =0\\
-2B+4C-2D & =0
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which we can solve in a number of ways.
 One solution is 
\begin_inset Formula $A=-1$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $B=2$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $C=1$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $D=0$
\end_inset

.
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-1(1+2t)+2(3+t-2t^{2})+(-5+4t^{2})+0(-5t-2t^{2})=0
\]

\end_inset

and we can write (for example) 
\begin_inset Formula $1+2t$
\end_inset

 as a linear combination of the others:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
1+2t=-2(3+t-2t^{2})-(-5+4t^{2})
\]

\end_inset


\series bold
[we could have chosen to write 
\begin_inset Formula $(3+t-2t^{2})$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $(-5+4t^{2})$
\end_inset

 as a linear combination of the others just as well]
\series default
.
 This means we can remove 
\begin_inset Formula $1+2t$
\end_inset

 from the set and retain its span.
 If the set of the three remaining vectors is linearly independent, it is
 a basis.
 If it is linearly dependent, we need to eliminate one of the vectors from
 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ 3+t-2t^{2},-5+4t^{2},-5t-2t^{2}\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 Repeating the above process without the polynomial 
\begin_inset Formula $1+2t$
\end_inset

 amounts to eliminating 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 from the equations: does 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
B(3+t-2t^{2})+C(-5+4t^{2})+D(-5t-2t^{2})=0
\]

\end_inset

have nontrivial solutions? We check as before by solving the linear system
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
3B-5C & =0\\
B-5D & =0\\
-2B+4C-2D & =0.
\end{align*}

\end_inset

One solution is 
\begin_inset Formula $B=5$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $C=3$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $D=1$
\end_inset

.
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
5(3+t-2t^{2})+3(-5+4t^{2})+(-5t-2t^{2})=0
\]

\end_inset

and we can write (for example) 
\begin_inset Formula $-5t-2t^{2}$
\end_inset

 as a linear combination of the others:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-5t-2t^{2}=-5(3+t-2t^{2})-3(-5+4t^{2})
\]

\end_inset


\series bold
[we could have chosen to write 
\begin_inset Formula $(3+t-2t^{2})$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $(-5+4t^{2})$
\end_inset

 as a linear combination of the others just as well]
\series default
.
 This means we can remove 
\begin_inset Formula $-5t-2t^{2}$
\end_inset

 from the set and retain its span, leaving two vectors (polynomials), 
\begin_inset Formula $(3+t-2t^{2})$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(-5+4t^{2})$
\end_inset

, that are not multiples of one another.
 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ 3+t-2t^{2},-5+4t^{2}\right\} $
\end_inset

 is a linearly independent subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 with the same span—a basis for the span of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 The dimension of the span is two.
\end_layout

