\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
-2\\
3
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

 as a linear combination of (the basis vectors) 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
-2
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{c}
5\\
-9
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

.
 In other words, we need to solve the equation
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{v}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
-2\\
3
\end{array}\right]=v_{1}\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
-2
\end{array}\right]+v_{2}\left[\begin{array}{c}
5\\
-9
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset

which is equivalent to solving
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 5\\
-2 & -9
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{c}
v_{1}\\
v_{2}
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{c}
-2\\
3
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

The solution can be found by row reduction:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 5 & -2\\
-2 & -9 & 3
\end{array}\right]\stackrel{2M_{1,:}+M_{2,:}\to M_{2,:}}{\longrightarrow}\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 5 & -2\\
0 & 1 & -1
\end{array}\right]\stackrel{-5M_{2,:}+M_{1,:}\to M_{1,:}}{\longrightarrow}\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
