\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
3 & -7 & -2\\
0 & 7 & -1\\
0 & 0 & 2
\end{array}\right]\mathbf{v}=\mathbf{w}$
\end_inset

.
 The vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{w}$
\end_inset

 can be determined quickly by writing down the sytem represented by 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & 0\\
-4 & 1 & 0\\
-2 & 2 & 1
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{c}
w_{1}\\
w_{2}\\
w_{3}
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{c}
0\\
6\\
14
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

 and using substitution:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
w_{1} & =0\\
-4w_{1}+w_{2} & =6\\
-2w_{1}+2w_{2}+w_{3} & =14
\end{align*}

\end_inset

